Span.Text: The use of mobile devices at the scene, enables the officer to capture evidence directly rather than writing notes and re-typing them later.  Photographic, audio and video evidence can be captured at the scene using the same digital device.
All notes are captured and stored in the cloud so they're immediately available for others to view.  Notes are captured at the scene, increasing the quality and saving time.

All information about a particular incident can be consolidated onto a single screen to make it easier for Officers to work with.  This includes all forms of evidence such as notes, audio, images and video.
